  "texts": [
    "We note that the seed length is O(log(n1)), but this does not always imply a short seed in practice.",
    "For instance, in our implementation with near-minimal entropy loss, the seed length exceeds the input length when n1 < 10 6 and m ≈ n1/2.",
    "Furthermore, it is often useful to assume that the output length m is proportional to the input length n1, i.e., m ∝ n1.",
    "In this case, the computation time for the Trevisan extractor becomes O(n2 1 log 2 n1), making it inefficient.",
